  "text": "Despite these advantages, ultrafiltration technology also has some drawbacks. In many cases, protein molecules are easily absorbed on to the surface of hydrophobic membranes, such as polyethersulfone (PES), resulting in fouling. As a consequence, membrane flux decreases drastically along with the operation time. Modification of membrane surface traits is one solution to minimize the fouling of the membrane surface [CITATION_1] 9 .",
